==English==

===Etymology===
[[portmanteau word|Portmanteau]] of [[metropolitan]] and [[heterosexual]].

===Noun===
{{en-noun|sg=[[metro-|metro]][[sexual]]}}
<!-- what is this? [[de:Metrosexualität]] -->

# A man concerned with self-image, by extension personal grooming, fashion, and aesthetics in general; who may or may not be concerned with self-indulgence and money. (Usually [[urban]], [[heterosexual]], often [[affluent]]). <!--  A concern for personal image is interpreted socially as being "homosexual" in some social circles, leaving "Gay Straight Male" as the logical terminology in that social context to describe a straight male concerned with fashion and personal appearance.-->
# A man who is seen, [[sociologically]], as having attributes common to [[homosexuals]], but is in fact [[heterosexual]].<sup>[http://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/Image:Metrosexual_Definition.JPG]</sup>

